        "content": "<p>How do I unravel the definition of inner product that I have managed to 'induce' on submodules? I include the code for this, and cannot move the demonstration that the inner product is 'what it is':</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">variable</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">W</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">submodule</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">instance</span> <span class=\"n\">submodule_inner_product_space</span>  <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_product_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"n\">inner_product_space.of_core</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">inner</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>  <span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"bp\">âŸª</span><span class=\"n\">v.1</span> <span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"n\">w.1</span><span class=\"bp\">âŸ«</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- âŸª(v:E) ,(w:E)âŸ«,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">conj_sym</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">intros</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">apply</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_conj_sym</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"o\">},</span> <span class=\"c1\">--Î» _ _ , inner_conj_sym _ _ ,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">nonneg_im</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">intro</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">apply</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_self_nonneg_im</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"o\">},</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- Î» _, inner_self_nonneg_im _ ,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">nonneg_re</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">intro</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">apply</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_self_nonneg</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"o\">},</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- Î» _, inner_self_nonneg ,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">definite</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">intros</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">hv</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"k\">have</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_self_eq_zero.mp</span> <span class=\"n\">hv</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">apply</span> <span class=\"n\">subtype.eq</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">rw</span> <span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"o\">,},</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">add_left</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">intros</span> <span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">exact</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_add_left</span><span class=\"o\">,},</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">smul_left</span>  <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">intros</span> <span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">exact</span> <span class=\"n\">inner_smul_left</span><span class=\"o\">,}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>this makes Lean happy enough, but now this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">W</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">submodule</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"bp\">âŸª</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"bp\">âŸ«</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"bp\">âŸª</span><span class=\"n\">x.val</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"n\">y.val</span><span class=\"bp\">âŸ«</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"o\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Indeed, how can I distinguish the one inner from the other, even?</p>",
